// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First instance, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent instances, use the carry from the previous instance
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the external carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the external carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    genvar i;

        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),

                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])

                    .a(a[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

```````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

``````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end

    endgenerate

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_array
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_array
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (

                    .b(b[3:0]),

                    .cout(carry[i]),

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );

                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from the previous stage

                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between BCD adders

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders use the carry-out from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
``````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the external carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

VERILOG CODE:
// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.

    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.

`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Intermediate carry signals

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_block
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99]; // Final carry-out
endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First instance, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent instances, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_array
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous stage
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );

    endgenerate

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i+3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99]; // Final carry-out
endmodule

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.

module top_module(

``````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    // Generate 100 instances of the bcd_fadd module
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (

Initiating comile/functionality check.
VERILOG CODE:
// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out
    assign cout = carry[99];

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])

                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

        end

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,

`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds

module bcd_fadd (

    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [100:0] carry; // Intermediate carry signals

    assign carry[0] = cin; // Initial carry-in

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            bcd_fadd adder (
                .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                .cin(carry[i]),
                .cout(carry[i+1]),
                .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
            );
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[100]; // Final carry-out

endmodule

```````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the external carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    genvar i;
    generate

            bcd_fadd adder (
                .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                .cin(carry[i]),
                .cout(carry[i+1]),

            );
        end

endmodule

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First instance uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent instances use the carry-out from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

VERILOG CODE:
// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

    wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between each BCD adder

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_chain
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, uses the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_instance (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out is the carry from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),

                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry wires

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99]; // Final carry-out
endmodule

    // Generate 100 instances of bcd_fadd
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adders
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First instance, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent instances, use the carry from the previous adder
                bcd_fadd adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99];

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

    genvar i;

        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,

    output cout,

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i+3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i+3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate
    
    assign cout = carry[99];

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),

                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])

            end
        end
    endgenerate

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (
    input [3:0] a,
    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry; // Intermediate carry signals

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    assign cout = carry[99]; // Final carry-out
endmodule

                .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                .cin(carry[i]),

        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder

//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors)

``````wire [99:0] carry; // Internal carry signals between BCD adders

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder_array
            if (i == 0) begin
                // First BCD adder, use the input carry-in
                bcd_fadd bcd_adder (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                // Subsequent BCD adders, use carry from previous adder
                bcd_fadd bcd_adder (
                    .a(a[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .b(b[i*4 +: 4]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[i*4 +: 4])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

    // The final carry-out from the last BCD adder
    assign cout = carry[99];

endmodule

// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,
    input     cin,
    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
``````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;
    
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate
    
    assign cout = carry[99];
endmodule

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,

    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
`````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;
    
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

// You are provided with a BCD one-digit adder named bcd_fadd that adds 
// two BCD digits and carry-in, and produces a sum and carry-out.

module bcd_fadd (

    input [3:0] b,

    output   cout,
    output [3:0] sum );
    
// Instantiate 100 copies of bcd_fadd to create a 100-digit BCD ripple-carry adder. 
//Your adder should add two 100-digit BCD numbers (packed into 400-bit vectors) 
//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.


// Hint: An instance array or generate statement would be useful here.

module top_module( 
    input [399:0] a, b,
    input cin,
    output cout,
    output [399:0] sum );
````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;
    
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate
    
    assign cout = carry[99];
endmodule

```````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````````wire [99:0] carry;
    
    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])

    genvar i;
    generate
        for (i = 0; i < 100; i = i + 1) begin: bcd_adder
            if (i == 0) begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[3:0]),
                    .b(b[3:0]),
                    .cin(cin),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[3:0])
                );
            end else begin
                bcd_fadd u_bcd_fadd (
                    .a(a[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .b(b[4*i + 3:4*i]),
                    .cin(carry[i-1]),
                    .cout(carry[i]),
                    .sum(sum[4*i + 3:4*i])
                );
            end
        end
    endgenerate

//and a carry-in to produce a 100-digit sum and carry out.
